    "title": "Basic Probability (Hard)",
    "body": "Probability measures how likely an event is, from 0 (impossible) to 1 (certain). For equally likely outcomes, it is the number of favorable outcomes divided by the total number of outcomes.",
    "key_points": [
      "P(event) = favorable ÷ total.",
      "Use the total count in the denominator.",
      "P(not event) = 1 − P(event)."
